<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1521,1252,1587]" box="[491,670,1563,1587]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
<bibRefCitation author="Hao D. - J. &amp; Fan B. - Q. &amp; Su P. &amp; Liu Q. &amp; Wang Y." box="[491,659,1563,1587]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" refId="ref16563" refString="Hao D. - J., Fan B. - Q., Su P., Liu Q., Wang Y. 2013. The flat mite Brevipalpus lewisi (Acari: Tenuipalpidae) infesting the Dawn Redwood Metasequoia glyptostroboides. Systematic and Applied Acarology," type="book" year="2013">
Hao 
<emphasis box="[542,596,1563,1587]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" box="[531,1513,1632,1657]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
Symptoms — This mite is an important pest of oranges, tangerines and lemons in 
<collectingRegion box="[1405,1513,1632,1656]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">California</collectingRegion>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="491" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" box="[491,1534,1667,1691]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
(
<collectingCountry box="[499,555,1667,1691]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">USA</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[620,683,1667,1690]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Serious injury has not been recorded on grape fruit. The mites lay their red,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
oval eggs singly in depressions and crevices of fruit, twigs and leaves, apparently preferring any stage of fruit to twigs or leaves. They seem to prefer the stem end of citrus fruit near or under the fruit button and fruit depressions and cause a silvering of the fruit. In central 
<collectingRegion box="[1397,1508,1770,1794]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">California</collectingRegion>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" box="[491,1526,1805,1830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">they overwinter in the adult stage. Peak populations are reached during the warmest months.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">Feeding on fruit produces scab-like scars, starting from fruit depressions or from depressions produced by leafhoppers or other insects, or by any injury that ruptures the oil sacs in the citrus peels. As the mites continue to feed, the scabbed area may increase to cover most of the fruit.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" box="[491,1469,1943,1968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
Damage results in reducing the grade of fruit (
<bibRefCitation author="Reuther W." box="[1023,1165,1943,1967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" pagination="383" refId="ref17574" refString="Reuther W. 1989. The Citrus Industry: Crop protection, postharvest technology and early history of citrus research in California. Vol 5. Ed: W. Reuther, E. C. Calavan, G. E. Carman. University of California, Division: pp 383." type="journal article" year="1989">Reuther, 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Jeppson L. R. &amp; Keifer H. H. &amp; Baker E. W." box="[1176,1364,1943,1967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" refId="ref16988" refString="Jeppson L. R., Keifer H. H., Baker E. W. 1975. Mites injurious to economic plants. University of California" type="book" year="1975">
Jeppson 
<emphasis box="[1251,1299,1943,1967]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">et al</emphasis>
., 1975
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Elmer H. S. &amp; Jeppson L. R." box="[1375,1469,1943,1967]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" refId="ref16290" refString="Elmer H. S., Jeppson L. R. 1957. Biology and control of the citrus flat mite. Elmer &amp; Jeppson, 1957." type="book" year="1957">Elmer &amp;</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" box="[491,1484,1978,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
Jeppson, 1957). In 
<collectingCountry box="[679,757,1978,2002]" name="Greece" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">Greece</collectingCountry>
, it is a pest of citrus, grapes, and pomegranates (
<bibRefCitation author="Hatzinikolis E. N." box="[1281,1473,1978,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" refId="ref16788" refString="Hatzinikolis E. N. 1986. The genus Brevipalpus in Greece (Acari: Tenuipalpidae). Entomologia Hellenica," type="book" year="1986">Hatzinikolis, 1986</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[491,1534,1632,2036]" lastBlockId="9.[491,1513,229,322]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="491" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">
<bibRefCitation author="Bytinski-Salez H." box="[491,719,2012,2036]" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" pagination="15 - 48" refId="ref15869" refString="Bytinski-Salez H. 1966. An annotated list of insects and mites introduced into Israel. Israel Journal of Entomology, 1: 15 - 48." type="journal article" year="1966">Bytinski-Salez (1966)</bibRefCitation>
reported it from “Blue Serbiam” vines in 
<quantity box="[1175,1245,2012,2036]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95808" pageId="7" pageNumber="489" unit="in" value="1952.0">1952 in</quantity>
<collectingCountry box="[1251,1313,2012,2036]" name="Israel" pageId="7" pageNumber="489">Israel</collectingCountry>
, causing severe leaf chlorosis. It was recently collected again from under side of petit vardo leaves infested with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ugarov &amp; Nikolskii" baseAuthorityYear="1937" box="[546,795,264,288]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Tetranychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="491" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turkestani">
<emphasis box="[546,795,264,288]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Tetranychus turkestani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Mizpe Ramon. It is not known as a vector of viruses (
<bibRefCitation author="Elmer H. S. &amp; Jeppson L. R." pageId="9" pageNumber="491" refId="ref16290" refString="Elmer H. S., Jeppson L. R. 1957. Biology and control of the citrus flat mite. Elmer &amp; Jeppson, 1957." type="book" year="1957">Elmer &amp; Jeppson, 1957</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
