<paragraph blockId="9.[491,1529,367,528]" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">
Biology and Ecology — 
<emphasis box="[795,928,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Overwinters</emphasis>
in adult stage on deciduous host plants such as grapes in California and is active throughout the year on citrus. Peak populations occur during warmest months (
<bibRefCitation author="Rice R. &amp; Weinberger G. B." box="[588,868,436,460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="491" pagination="25 - 26" refId="ref17627" refString="Rice R., Weinberger G. B. 1981. Citrus flat mite on pistachios in California. California Agriculture, 35 (7): 25 - 26." type="journal article" year="1981">Rice &amp; Weinberger, 1981</bibRefCitation>
). Number of annual generations is related to the 
<typeStatus box="[1418,1462,436,460]" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">type</typeStatus>
of host, for example 4 on vines in 
<collectingCountry box="[821,918,470,494]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and California. It reproduces by thelytoky, as no males were found (
<bibRefCitation author="Buchanan G. A. &amp; Begston M. &amp; Exley E. M." box="[631,854,504,528]" pageId="9" pageNumber="491" refId="ref15820" refString="Buchanan G. A., Begston M., Exley E. M. 1980. Population growth of Brevipalpus lewisi McGregor" type="book" year="1980">
Buchanan 
<emphasis box="[740,787,504,528]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="491">et al</emphasis>
., 1980
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
